{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:42:07.985Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In data pipelines for ML engineering, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "joins"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are two fundamental operations in pandas for aggregating and combining data: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " splits a DataFrame into groups based on column values, applies aggregation functions (sum, mean, count, etc.) to each group, and combines the results; "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "joins"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (via "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pd.merge()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ") combine data from two or more DataFrames based on a common column, similar to SQL joins."}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple definition:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " “The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " function lets you split your DataFrame into groups based on one or more columns. Then you can apply aggregation functions (sum, mean, count, etc.) to each group.” “Joins let you combine data from two or more DataFrames based on a common column. Think of it like SQL joins.”"}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "pandas groupby/joins — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pandas "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Split-Apply-Combine"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " does"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " operation has "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "three steps"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (the \"split-apply-combine\" paradigm):"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Split"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Divide the DataFrame into groups based on values in a column (or multiple columns)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Apply"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Apply an aggregation or transformation function to each group"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Combine"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Merge the results back into a new DataFrame"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Basic "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " syntax"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import pandas as pd\n\ndf = pd.read_csv(\"sales.csv\")\n\n# Group by single column and calculate mean\ndf.groupby('category')['value'].mean()\n\n# Output:\n# category\n# A  10.5\n# B  20.3\n# C  15.7"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Group by multiple columns"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Group by multiple columns for finer-grained analysis\ndf.groupby(['category', 'region'])['value'].sum()\n\n# Output:\n# category  region\n# A         North   50.2\n#           South   30.5\n# B         North   80.1\n#           South   40.3"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common aggregation functions"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Multiple aggregations in one line\ndf.groupby('category')['value'].agg(['sum', 'mean', 'count', 'nunique'])\n\n# Output:\n#          sum   mean  count  nunique\n# category\n# A        52.5  10.5     5        3\n# B        81.2  20.3     4        2"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Common aggregations"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "sum()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Sum of values\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "mean()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Average\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "count()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Number of rows\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "nunique()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Number of unique values\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "min()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "max()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Min/max values\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "std()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Standard deviation"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step-by-step: How "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " works"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Creating the Grouped Object"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "grouped = df.groupby('Category')"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This creates a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "DataFrameGroupBy"}, {"type": "text", "text": " object that contains all grouping information but "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "doesn't compute"}, {"type": "text", "text": " anything yet."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If you print "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "grouped"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", you'll see a reference to the groupby object, not actual data."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Applying an Aggregation Function"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "result = grouped.sum()   # Trigger computation\nresult = grouped.mean()\nresult = grouped.count()"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Applying an aggregation triggers the computation and returns a DataFrame with the grouped result."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Inspecting Groups"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (optional)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Iterate over groups\nfor name, group in grouped:\n    print(name)\n    print(group)\n\n# Access specific group directly\ngroup_a = grouped.get_group('A')"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pandas Joins (merging DataFrames)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What joins do"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Joins combine two or more DataFrames based on a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "common column"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (key), similar to SQL JOINs. Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pd.merge()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to perform joins."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Basic merge syntax"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "merged_df = pd.merge(df1, df2, on='common_column', how='inner')"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "on"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Column name to join on"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "how"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Type of join ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "'inner'"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "'left'"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "'right'"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "'outer'"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Types of Joins"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Inner Join"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (most common)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Returns "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "only rows where the key exists in both DataFrames"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (intersection)."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "df1 = pd.DataFrame({\n    'Key': ['A', 'B', 'C', 'D'],\n    'Value1': [1, 2, 3, 4]\n})\n\ndf2 = pd.DataFrame({\n    'Key': ['B', 'D', 'E', 'F'],\n    'Value2': [5, 6, 7, 8]\n})\n\ninner_merged = pd.merge(df1, df2, on='Key', how='inner')\nprint(inner_merged)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "  Key  Value1  Value2\n0   B       2       5\n1   D       4       6"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Only rows with keys "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "'B'"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "'D'"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (present in both) are kept."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Left Join"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Returns "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "all rows from the left DataFrame"}, {"type": "text", "text": " plus matched rows from the right. Unmatched rows have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "NaN"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for missing values."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "left_merged = pd.merge(df1, df2, on='Key', how='left')\nprint(left_merged)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "  Key  Value1  Value2\n0   A       1     NaN\n1   B       2     5.0\n2   C       3     NaN\n3   D       4     6.0"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All keys from "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "df1"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are kept; unmatched rows ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "'A'"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "'C'"}, {"type": "text", "text": ") have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "NaN"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Value2"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Right Join"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Returns "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "all rows from the right DataFrame"}, {"type": "text", "text": " plus matched rows from the left. Unmatched rows have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "NaN"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for missing values."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "right_merged = pd.merge(df1, df2, on='Key', how='right')\nprint(right_merged)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "  Key  Value1  Value2\n0   B       2       5\n1   D       4       6\n2   E     NaN       7\n3   F     NaN       8"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All keys from "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "df2"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are kept; unmatched rows ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "'E'"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "'F'"}, {"type": "text", "text": ") have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "NaN"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Value1"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Outer Join"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Returns "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "all rows from both DataFrames"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Missing values are filled with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "NaN"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (union)."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "outer_merged = pd.merge(df1, df2, on='Key', how='outer')\nprint(outer_merged)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "  Key  Value1  Value2\n0   A       1     NaN\n1   B       2     5.0\n2   C       3     NaN\n3   D       4     6.0\n4   E     NaN     7.0\n5   F     NaN     8.0"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All keys from both "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "df1"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "df2"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are kept."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Joining on indexes"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "You can also join by "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "index"}, {"type": "text", "text": " instead of columns:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "df1 = pd.DataFrame({'Value1': [1, 2, 3]}, index=['A', 'B', 'C'])\ndf2 = pd.DataFrame({'Value2': [4, 5, 6]}, index=['B', 'C', 'D'])\n\n# Join by index\njoined = df1.join(df2, on=None, how='outer')"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Or use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pd.merge()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "left_index=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "right_index=True"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "link", "attrs": {"href": "https://www.bmc.com/blogs/pandas-group-merge-concatenate-join/", "target": "_blank", "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow", "class": "text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400", "title": null}}], "text": "bmc"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Concatenating DataFrames"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pd.concat()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is another way to combine DataFrames, like "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "inner/outer joins of sets"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Concatenate along rows (axis=0)\ncombined = pd.concat([df1, df2], axis=0)\n\n# Concatenate along columns (axis=1)\ncombined = pd.concat([df1, df2], axis=1)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Inner join"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (intersection) vs "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "outer join"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (union) of sets. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "link", "attrs": {"href": "https://www.bmc.com/blogs/pandas-group-merge-concatenate-join/", "target": "_blank", "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow", "class": "text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400", "title": null}}], "text": "bmc"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Groupby + Join workflow"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "You can combine "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "join"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for complex pipelines:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Step 1: Group by category and aggregate\nldf = df.groupby('category')['value'].agg(['sum', 'mean']).reset_index()\n\n# Step 2: Join with another DataFrame\nrdf = pd.DataFrame({\n    'category': ['A', 'B', 'C', 'D'],\n    'currency': ['USD', 'EUR', 'GBP', 'JPY']\n})\n\n# Step 3: Perform left join\njdf = pd.merge(ldf, rdf, on='category', how='left')"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Benefits"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Groups data, aggregates, then joins with reference data\n- Ensures all currency codes are present in the result"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and joins"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Know which join type you need"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Join type"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keep only matching keys"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "inner"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keep all left keys + matches"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "left"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keep all right keys + matches"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "right"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keep all keys from both"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "outer"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[euron](https://euron.one/community/posts/ccf8e119-7354-4e97-8319-6fd8a99bfcf6)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "reset_index()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " after "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "After aggregation, the result has group labels as the index:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# With index (default)\nresult = df.groupby('category')['value'].mean()\nprint(result.index)  # ['A', 'B', 'C']\n\n# Reset to column\nresult = df.groupby('category')['value'].mean().reset_index()\nprint(result.columns)  # ['category', 'value']"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Makes it easier to join with other DataFrames."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Check for missing values after joins"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Check unmatched keys\nunmatched = jdf[jdf['currency'].isna()]\nprint(unmatched)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Join on columns, not indexes (usually)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For clarity and maintainability, explicitly specify "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "on='column_name'"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " splits data into groups, applies aggregations (sum, mean, count, nunique), and combines results using the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "split-apply-combine"}, {"type": "text", "text": " paradigm."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Joins"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (via "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pd_merge()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ") combine DataFrames based on a common column, with four types: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "inner"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "left"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "right"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "outer"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Inner join"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is most common (keeps only matching keys); "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "left join"}, {"type": "text", "text": " keeps all left keys; "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "outer join"}, {"type": "text", "text": " keeps all keys from both."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "reset_index()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " after "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to convert group labels to columns for easier joining."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "You can combine "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " + "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "join"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for complex pipelines: aggregate → join → validate."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Understanding different join types is crucial for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "not losing or misrepresenting data"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In data pipelines: use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "groupby"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "aggregation and pattern discovery"}, {"type": "text", "text": "; use joins for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "consolidating related data from different sources"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}]}]}]}}